Great thin crust pizza!
Dells has been around forever in Casa Grande and it looks it!!
The building is old and dingy, and still has smoke stains on the walls and sports pennants that litter them.
It's definitely is an old school sports bar.
The wait staff is pretty decent., but plan a long wait on busy nights.
They have your typical bar food on the menu, but it's their thin crust pizza that brings people back.
Not too thin and flakey and it doesn't taste like cardboard like other places.
Good sauce and toppings.
For a twist, try their sausage and sauerkraut pizza.
It's actually pretty darn good!

