Where to start?
Sandy, the owner, is still a nasty old broad who does not have time for you, unless you are in the "circle" of favorite customers and friends.
The building is dark and musty, dust sticks to the walls thicker then the paint.
The satellite dish kiosk is way out of place.
I wondered if the staff gets a commission if they sale a system or TV.
The bartender tried really hard to sale me a TV last time I stopped by.
The piizza is bland...
I think that the sauce is plain, straight tomato paste.
Stay away from the beer on tap, because it is always warm.
The employees always have something to complain about, and they don't mind giving you all the gory details.
Save your money for a much better pizza from Papa Murphy's.

